<paragraph blockId="119.[189,1398,910,1018]" lastBlockId="120.[189,1399,267,329]" lastPageId="120" lastPageNumber="121" pageId="119" pageNumber="120">Acrostichal and dorsocentral bristles undifferentiated. Hind femur and tibia somewhat brownish on middle. Male: hind tibia slightly curved, anteriorly on apical half without squamiform setae, but with a row of spinule-like setae. Abdomen with vessel-like glandular structure opening between tergites 4 and 5.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
